We recommended and Management agreed that the Municipal Treasurer:

deposit immediately the accumulated collections amounting to ₱46,274.03 and;
Henceforth, deposit collections daily and intact, pursuant to the above-mentioned rules and regulations.

We recommended the following:
The Municipal Mayor immediately create Inventory Committee to conduct annual physical count of local road network and accordingly update the RPCLRN and local road map of the Municipality;
The Municipal Mayor direct the Municipal Engineer and the Municipal Accountant to locate the records where the necessary data can be sourced to complete the details and specifications of the roads and their components to facilitate in the preparation and maintenance of the required records and reports and computation of depreciation;
Personnel concerned prepare and maintain the required records and reports for all roads and their components – Registry of Public Infrastructures for Roads, Subsidiary Ledgers, Local Road Network Property Cards, Local Road Inventory, Road Map, Report on Local Road Network and year-end Report of RPCLRN; and
The Municipal Accountant to include in the Notes to Financial Statements necessary details of the local roads recorded in the books as prescribed in COA Circular No. 2015-008.

Considering the foregoing deficiencies, we recommended and Management agreed that the Members of the BAC:
Submit the Technical Specifications of goods, Scope of works for service and ABC for the seven procurements;
Submit the minutes of meeting and attendance for the pre-procurement and pre-bid conferences for the two contracts noted, if such were conducted, as well as, the certification for the posting requirements if complied;
Submit the lacking documents of the contract for the infrastructure projects identified in paragraph 13.25;
Henceforth, ensure that invitations in writing are sent to observers at least five days before the conduct of the required procurement activity and attach the duly received invitation letters as part of bidding documents; and
Ensure that complete documents to support the contract preparation and signing of procurement of infrastructure projects are prepared by the winning bidders and to be attached to the contract documents.

We recommended and Management agreed that:
Management identify the sources funds charged for the projects implemented without AIP (paragraph 25.6);
Henceforth, the Municipal Mayor ensure implementation of all development projects within the timeline set in the Annual Investment Plan and those remained unimplemented from prior years;
The Municipal Planning and Development Coordinator monitor and evaluate the implementation of the development projects in accordance with the approved development plan; and
Management prepare annual accomplishment report identifying the status of the projects as of year-end for current year including subsequent periods with unimplemented projects.

We have recommended that the Municipality:

consider replacing instead of repairing the old motor vehicles and heavy equipment which are beyond economic repair to avoid extravagant disbursements on repairs and maintenance;

secure and submit proof of ownership of the new ambulance for proper recognition in the accounting books.

We have recommended that the management:

Justify the noted lapses;

Immediately transfer the needed funds from the general fund to replenish the trust fund account;

Utilize funds for the specific purpose that it was created or appropriated for in consonance with Section 305 (a) of the RA No. 7160.

We recommended that the Municipal Mayor directs the:
Municipal Engineer and the Municipal General Services Officer (Municipal Treasurer) conduct a yearly physical count of local road network projects and accordingly maintain an update local road map of the MLGU;
Municipal General Services Officer (Municipal Treasurer) to maintain a Local Road Inventory and Road Map and keep a complete Local Road Network Property Card for all roads and its components;
Municipal Accountant to trace the recorded road, highways and bridges which were closed to government equity prior to 2016 and subsequently record in its books of accounts the amount of road works equivalent to the required transition provision, keep and maintain Registry of Public Infrastructures for Road and subsidiary records for roads and road components for every road network and provide for the depreciation for the local road network;
Municipal Engineer to provide the Municipal Accountant and the General Services Officer with the complete description and cost segregation of road components for road projects; and
Municipal Accountant to include in the Notes to Financial Statements necessary details of the local roads recorded in the books as prescribed in COA Circular No. 2015-008.

